d_m
\Bbb R^2
d_m(x,y) = max \lbrace|x_1 - y_1| , |x_2 -y_2| \rbrace 
x=(x_1,x_2) , y = (y_1 ,y_2)
d(x,y) \leq d(x,z) + d(z,y)
i =1 , 2 
|x_i -  y_i| = |x_i -z_i +z_i -y_i|\\               \leq |x_i -z_i|+|z_i -y_i|
d_m(x,y) \leq d_m(x,z) +d_m(z,y)
 d(x,y) = \max\{|x_1-y_1|,|x_2-y_2|\} \le \max\{|x_1 - z_1| + |z_1-y_1|,|x_2-z_2| + |z_2-y_2|\} \le \max\{|x_1 - z_1|,|x_2-z_2|\} + \max\{|z_1-y_1|,|z_2-y_2|\} = d(x,z) + d(z,y). 
